# Deploy next steps

After completing any code change in this repo, **always** end the response with a **What to do next** section.

The user's workflow: push from local machine, then pull and restart on the AWS EC2 server.

## Required closing section format

Include concrete commands, not vague "deploy when ready":

**Local (push):**
```bash
git add -A
git commit -m "your message"
git push
```

**Server (pull & restart):**
```bash
cd /opt/toms-sms
git pull
npm install          # only if package.json changed
npm run db:migrate   # only if migrations changed
npm run build
sudo systemctl restart toms-sms
```

Omit steps that clearly don't apply (e.g. skip `npm install` for UI-only changes). Mention if the user needs to hard-refresh the ServiceM8 add-on iframe to see UI changes.

Apply even for small fixes. Skip only for pure questions with no code changes.
